{
  "texts": [
    "Conversational AI tools such as GPT and Gemini can be used to generate realistic case scenarios, interpret responses, ask queries, and offer feedback, allowing students to practice clinical reasoning, history-taking, decision-making, and communication skills in a secure and controlled environment [76,77].",
    "For example, students could interact with a virtual patient who has shoulder pain and go through the diagnostic steps to establish whether it is a rotator cuff tear or another condition.",
    "Generative AI tools can prepare students for real-world practice by simulating clinical decision-making, offering feedback, and providing interactive case studies that cover diagnostic processes, treatment alternatives, and ethical issues.",
    "Moreover, AI could present rare or complex orthopedic conditions that students might not frequently encounter during their training, thus broadening their clinical exposure and preparedness.",
    "Allison et al."
  ]
}